From Molly Kilete, Abuja Please enable JavaScript This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. The Inspector General of Police (IGP), Usman Baba, has presented a check of N13 billion to the families of police officers killed between 2012-2020. The amount also covers personnel who got injured while carrying out their duties between 2012-2021. Over 6,000, families of slain personnel are expected to benefit from the money.